{"id":66031,"title":"Kidney cancer: progress and controversies in neoadjuvant therapy.","abstract":"Use of clinically active agents, such as kinase inhibitors, before nephrectomy is safe and feasible and can decrease the size of primary tumours, enabling optimization of the surgical approach. However, the overall clinical benefit of the neoadjuvant use of toxic drugs, such as axitinib, has not yet been demonstrated.","date":"2014-05-14","categories":"Male Urogenital Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24752207","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.797998,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Neoadjuvant therapy","weight":0.723939,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neoadjuvant_therapy"},{"name":"Kidney","weight":0.72365,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidney"},{"name":"Tumor","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tumor"},{"name":"Kidney cancer","weight":0.688855,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidney_cancer"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.678276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Toxicity","weight":0.495417,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toxicity"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.489611,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Axitinib","weight":0.268791,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Axitinib"},{"name":"Enzyme inhibitor","weight":0.153909,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enzyme_inhibitor"},{"name":"Nephrectomy","weight":0.0972222,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nephrectomy"},{"name":"Kinase","weight":0.0503109,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kinase"},{"name":"Controversy","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Controversy"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","we